climbs.name: Foxtrot
climbs.fa: Matthew Beeson, December 2020 (unless anyone knows otherwise)

content.description: Stand start high on a left hand side-pull and a right hand sloper with a thumb-catch under, which kind of makes a good pinch. Get your feet set, and move right to a gaston. Finish up the sketchy slab. Scope it out first unless you are very comfortable on slab.Project--Start lower, either using terrible underclings or a far right hand sloper and a left hand pinch. Or however you want, it's V-not possible for me.
content.location: In about the center of the boulder to the left of the viney crack. Currently the only spot where the top-out is cleaned.

content.description: Slightly overhanging boulder at the start, with a slab finish. Currently overgrown, one cleaned  line in the center of the boulder. Likely a few other lines there if you want to clear some vines and thorns.
